06/07/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Romania and Hungary will modernise all interstate border checkpoints within two years, according to an agreement reached Monday (5 July) between Romanian Prime Minister Adrian Nastase and his Hungarian counterpart, Peter Medgyessy. The two met in Oradea to discuss bilateral issues and to attend the opening of the Secuieni-Letavertes border checkpoint, where customs control is being performed jointly. (Rompres, Mediafax - 05/07/04)
